content: Yes, The Beatles' rooftop concert is a legendary performance that took place on January 30, 1969. The band played on the rooftop of their Apple Corps headquarters in London, performing a set of nine songs. The concert lasted for approximately 42 minutes before being shut down by the police due to noise complaints. Some of the songs performed included "Get Back," "Don't Let Me Down," and "I've Got a Feeling." It's a unique and memorable performance that many Beatles' fans consider to be one of their greatest live shows.
